column1: Supplementary Table 7. Genes in DEPICT-defined loci
Each row corresponds to a gene in one of the DEPICT-defined loci. A gene with NA in the final three columns is not present in the DEPICT inventory.
Such a gene may overlap more than one DEPICT-defined locus, and in such cases we kept the row with the smallest GWAS P value.
Locus, the locus where the gene is located, identified by the DEPICT-defined lead SNPs defining it;
Nr.of.genes.in.locus, the number of genes in the DEPICT inventory overlapping the locus;
Chromosome.and.position, the coordinates of the locus endpoints;
GWAS.P-value, the P value of the most significant SNP in the locus;
Ensembl.gene.ID, the Ensembl identifier of the gene, which may be more stable than the HUGO identifier;
Gene.symbol, the HUGO identifier of the gene employed by DEPICT;
Gene.closest.to.lead.SNP, whether the gene is the one with start site closest to any one of the lead SNPs in the locus;
False.discovery.rate, the FDR associated with the gene P value discretized to four levels (<0.01, 0.01<=FDR<0.05, 0.05<=FDR<0.20, >=0.20).
Results based on the full GWAS summary statistics (N = 1,131,881).
